 the statement.\", \"from\": 3243, \"to\": 3490, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3286, \"end\": 3298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haute-Savoie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Haute-Savoie\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haute-Savoie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haute-Savoie\"}, {\"begin\": 3326, \"end\": 3332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9826101515801768, \"rank\": 0.01769562014351708, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3417, \"end\": 3421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.426204568153648e-70, \"text\": \"ISIS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"German police have also publicized two incidents allegedly involving four teenagers.\", \"from\": 3492, \"to\": 3576, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3492, \"end\": 3498, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.999763359341636, \"rank\": 0.00022932790351213233, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Officials in Dusseldorf said in April they arrested\\u00a0three teenagers, a 15-year-old boy and girl, and a 16year-old girl, accused of planning a terror attack.\", \"from\": 3577, \"to\": 3733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3590, \"end\": 3600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/D\\u00fcsseldorf\", \"score\": 0.9999070811753292, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dusseldorf\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/D\\u00fcsseldorf\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/D\\u00fcsseldorf\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another alleged plot involving a possible knife attack on a Heidelberg synagogue, which was disrupted in May, involved an 18-year-old man, a German prosecutor's statement said.\", \"from\": 3735, \"to\": 3911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3795, \"end\": 3805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heidelberg\", \"score\": 0.9999937750329111, \"rank\": 6.224976659324737e-06, \"text\": \"Heidelberg\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heidelberg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heidelberg\"}, {\"begin\": 3876, \"end\": 3882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.999763359341636, \"rank\": 0.00022932790351213233, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Swiss police in March arrested a 15-year-old Swiss boy and a 16-year-old Italian boy for ISIS support and plotting bomb attacks, according to a police statement.\", \"from\": 3913, \"to\": 4074, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3913, \"end\": 3925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_Switzerland\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Swiss police\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 3958, \"end\": 3963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9999999990850483, \"rank\": 9.147260590132967e-10, \"text\": \"Swiss\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 3986, \"end\": 3993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9306254217625854, \"rank\": 0.0626977378398397, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4002, \"end\": 4006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.426204568153648e-70, \"text\": \"ISIS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And in May, a 14-year-old girl from Montenegro was arrested for plotting an attack in Austria, which was allegedly ISIS-inspired, with a knife and axe already purchased.\", \"from\": 4076, \"to\": 4245, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4112, \"end\": 4122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montenegro\", \"score\": 0.9999992026654122, \"rank\": 7.446259018859857e-07, \"text\": \"Montenegro\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montenegro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montenegro\"}, {\"begin\": 4162, \"end\": 4169, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\", \"score\": 0.9999247013467629, \"rank\": 7.254017785400947e-05, \"text\": \"Austria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While these alleged plots involving teenagers do not appear to involve ISIS-K specifically, the spread of the newer ISIS affiliate presents a simultaneous and novel challenge for Western intelligence agencies.\", \"from\": 4247, \"to\": 4456, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4318, \"end\": 4324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"score\": 0.9965712144984205, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ISIS-K\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\"}, {\"begin\": 4363, \"end\": 4367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.426204568153648e-70, \"text\": \"ISIS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ISIS-K recruits predominantly stem not from the Arabic-speaking world, but from Central Asia, and include Russian-speaking Tajik citizens.\", \"from\": 4457, \"to\": 4595, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4457, \"end\": 4463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"score\": 0.9965712144984205, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ISIS-K\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\"}, {\"begin\": 4580, \"end\": 4585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajikistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999990359356, \"rank\": 9.636966448777495e-10, \"text\": \"Tajik\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajikistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajikistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bordering Afghanistan, where ISIS-K first emerged, Tajikistan has long struggled with a mix of poverty, intense political repression by its government, backed by Moscow, and a broad spectrum of Islamism from across the fervently religious region.\", \"from\": 4597, \"to\": 4843, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4607, \"end\": 4618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999992960511, \"rank\": 7.041383266375388e-10, \"text\": \"Afghanistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}, {\"begin\": 4626, \"end\": 4632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"score\": 0.9965712144984205, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ISIS-K\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\"}, {\"begin\": 4648, \"end\": 4658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajikistan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7215243258825802e-17, \"text\": \"Tajikistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajikistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajikistan\"}, {\"begin\": 4759, \"end\": 4765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9417942009332524e-13, \"text\": \"Moscow\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\"}, {\"begin\": 4791, \"end\": 4799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2394329193741531e-21, \"text\": \"Islamism\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Analysts say the Tajik minority in Afghanistan is also less represented by the Pashto Taliban government, adding to the anger at discrimination felt by Tajiks across the former Soviet Union.\", \"from\": 4844, \"to\": 5034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4861, \"end\": 4866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajikistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999990359356, \"rank\": 9.636966448777495e-10, \"text\": \"Tajik\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajikistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajikistan\"}, {\"begin\": 4879, \"end\": 4890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999992960511, \"rank\": 7.041383266375388e-10, \"text\": \"Afghanistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}, {\"begin\": 4923, \"end\": 4929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pashtuns\", \"score\": 0.976519048854731, \"rank\": 0.024045304222475892, \"text\": \"Pashto\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pashtuns\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pashtuns\"}, {\"begin\": 4930, \"end\": 4937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taliban\", \"score\": 0.9975392563040291, \"rank\": 0.002466813844359812, \"text\": \"Taliban\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taliban\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taliban\"}, {\"begin\": 4996, \"end\": 5002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajiks\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9410201712942895e-34, \"text\": \"Tajiks\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajiks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajiks\"}, {\"begin\": 5028, \"end\": 5033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1006986571463821e-21, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ISIS-K threat has also moved swiftly closer to Europe, as a wide wave of arrests in Turkey has exposed.\", \"from\": 5036, \"to\": 5143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5124, \"end\": 5130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4358608539903533e-17, \"text\": \"Turkey\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An 87-page indictment, relating to the detention of 18 ISIS-K suspects, many of them Tajik, for an alleged terror conspiracy involving training, support and an attack on the Swedish consulate in Istanbul, gives a rare window into the \\\"black box\\\" of ISIS-K plotting.\", \"from\": 5144, \"to\": 5409, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5199, \"end\": 5205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"score\": 0.9965712144984205, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ISIS-K\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\"}, {\"begin\": 5318, \"end\": 5325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\", \"score\": 0.9998737507369038, \"rank\": 0.00012607693445441674, \"text\": \"Swedish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\"}, {\"begin\": 5339, \"end\": 5347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\", \"score\": 0.9999999999581632, \"rank\": 3.946040040131377e-11, \"text\": \"Istanbul\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\"}, {\"begin\": 5393, \"end\": 5399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"score\": 0.9965712144984205, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ISIS-K\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It reveals how a shadowy figure, known to the detainees as \\\"Rustam,\\\" directs plots in the West - and training for them - from the Afghanistan-Pakistan border.\", \"from\": 5410, \"to\": 5568, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5540, \"end\": 5567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Durand_Line\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Afghanistan-Pakistan border\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Durand_Line\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Durand_Line\"}, {\"begin\": 5540, \"end\": 5567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Durand_Line\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Afghanistan-Pakistan border\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Durand_Line\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Durand_Line\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The indictment says: \\\"Rustam/R\\u00fcstem (K) is the Tajik who is the current head of the ISKP Foreign Operations unit.\\\"\", \"from\": 5570, \"to\": 5684, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5617, \"end\": 5622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajikistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999990359356, \"rank\": 9.636966448777495e-10, \"text\": \"Tajik\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajikistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajikistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The indictment quotes one suspect saying Rustam used multiple, changing handles on the Telegram messaging app.\", \"from\": 5685, \"to\": 5795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5726, \"end\": 5732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rostam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1832262887341616e-24, \"text\": \"Rustam\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rostam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rostam\"}, {\"begin\": 5772, \"end\": 5780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Telegraphy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.2194625817632045e-27, \"text\": \"Telegram\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Telegraphy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Telegraphy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Generally, Rustam deletes the telegram every 15-20 days as a precaution,\\\" the detainee said.\", \"from\": 5796, \"to\": 5889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5808, \"end\": 5814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rostam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1832262887341616e-24, \"text\": \"Rustam\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rostam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rostam\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"After I deleted it, he would contact me with another username.\\\"\", \"from\": 5890, \"to\": 5954, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Several of the detainees refer to Rustam as an external operations and explosives director for ISIS-K. Last week, 13 of the accused in this case were sentenced for between six to 10 years for involvement in the plot, while another three were set free.\", \"from\": 5955, \"to\": 6206, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5989, \"end\": 5995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rostam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1832262887341616e-24, \"text\": \"Rustam\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rostam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rostam\"}, {\"begin\": 6050, \"end\": 6056, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"score\": 0.9965712144984205, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ISIS-K\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The indictment, first reported in Turkish media, also describes, through the testimony of detainees, how a conveyor belt of ISIS-K recruits moves through an array of hotels in Istanbul.\", \"from\": 6208, \"to\": 6393, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6242, \"end\": 6249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 0.9999998347602878, \"rank\": 1.640947621087378e-07, \"text\": \"Turkish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}, {\"begin\": 6332, \"end\": 6338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"score\": 0.9965712144984205, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ISIS-K\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\"}, {\"begin\": 6384, \"end\": 6392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\", \"score\": 0.9999999999581632, \"rank\": 3.946040040131377e-11, \"text\": \"Istanbul\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some then go via Iran to receive training in Afghanistan.\", \"from\": 6394, \"to\": 6451, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6411, \"end\": 6415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.9999999999918145, \"rank\": 7.809989194195018e-12, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}, {\"begin\": 6439, \"end\": 6450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999992960511, \"rank\": 7.041383266375388e-10, \"text\": \"Afghanistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Others travel freely back and forth to Russia, where ISIS-K killed 137 people in a horrific attack on the Crocus City Hall in Moscow in March.\", \"from\": 6452, \"to\": 6594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6491, \"end\": 6497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999699867, \"rank\": 2.5192190931878837e-11, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 6505, \"end\": 6511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"score\": 0.9965712144984205, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ISIS-K\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\"}, {\"begin\": 6558, \"end\": 6569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Crocus_City_Mall\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Crocus City\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Crocus_City_Mall\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Crocus_City_Mall\"}, {\"begin\": 6578, \"end\": 6584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9417942009332524e-13, \"text\": \"Moscow\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The extent of ISIS-K's use of Turkey as a transit hub is acknowledged by officials in the Turkish indictment.\", \"from\": 6596, \"to\": 6705, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6610, \"end\": 6616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"score\": 0.9965712144984205, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ISIS-K\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\"}, {\"begin\": 6626, \"end\": 6632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4358608539903533e-17, \"text\": \"Turkey\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}, {\"begin\": 6686, \"end\": 6693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 0.9999998347602878, \"rank\": 1.640947621087378e-07, \"text\": \"Turkish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Central Asian Foreign Terrorist fighters could use the Turkey-Iran route in 2023, this could lead not only to prestige loss for our country but also, there is the threat that these elements could look to carry out a large scale (blockbuster/mega) action in our country,\\\" the indictment says.\", \"from\": 6706, \"to\": 6998, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6707, \"end\": 6720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Asia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9718271813589237e-24, \"text\": \"Central Asian\",